Watch on youtube: https://youtu.be/kgVyx9IqGM0 Tags: 3dprint , strength test , material test , prusament , nylon , Prusament PA11-CF is a nylon filament reinforced with carbon fibers. In this video I am measuring its mechanical properties and comparing them with PC Blend CF. Prusa also has a new print sheet developed for nylon filaments. All objects are printed on Prusa MK3S 3D printer equipped with hardened nozzle. Temperatures inside DIY Ikea lack enclosure was 45°C. Tested products: PA11-CF: https://www.prusa3d.com/product/prusament-pa11-carbon-fiber-black-800g/ PA sheet: https://www.prusa3d.com/product/double-sided-powder-coated-pa-nylon-spring-steel-sheet/ Download results below this text.
